<subSubSection pageNumber="768" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="768">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="768">Note:</emphasis>
Boyce &amp; Hay disagree with 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Merrill’s">Merrill's</normalizedToken>
interpretation of the cited Rumphius plate, excluding t. 181, f. 2 (which is a 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Pothos" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="768">Pothos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and follow Roxburgh in restricting the Linnaean name to t. 181, f. 1, which they identify as a species of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Piperaceae" genus="Piper" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="768">Piper</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Piperaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Piperaceae</taxonomicName>
). Although they wrongly accept 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Roxburgh’s">Roxburgh's</normalizedToken>
implicit typification, their statement that it is &quot;here confirmed&quot; is accepted as a formal typification (Art. 7.11).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
